reviewText: Found this DVD in good condition and the story line a bit "Hammering". The unique way the facts do seem to all have an unknown mystery is okay and many I feel would get a great deal of entertainment out of the-endless-facts. But,do have to make a point that the narrators persistance and almost "begging" way of demanding(through script)you to pay attention and "be-open" to an obvious only untill the end of the show "no" answer to it all conclusion these days makes me a little naucious.Which maybe I don't get but if there isn't a conclusion,just leaves me feeling lyed to and w/a headache-and a "Big" waste of time.Like I said it is interesting summing up all the facts and would make some feel as if they're minds are opened up wider for watching all of it. Which is why I still give it a Four Star Rating... But for my prefferences,got a headache,felt as though I'd been knocked off center,a waste of time and learned to hate the assigned narrator-being over middle aged myself,leads me to believe he needs to retire. A debutaunt worthy only of the french revolution(in otherwords-Out Dated and asking "Why don't they eat cake???")... . But,either way, if you'd like to learn facts in a Hopscotch mannor and you enjoy "Hipe!" and having something new to bring to talk about around the barber shop,then this one's for you.It's a three disc set and is packaged well and still fits in your DVD cabinet. On a lighter foot it does entertain and will keep your kids' happy for hours. :)
